    <prp:abstract>We propose to spatially resolve the newly discovered millimeter SiO and CH3OH mega-masers in  nearby type II AGN NGC1068 with ALMA. With the high resolution data from ALMA, we will not only confirm the detections of these two new mega-maser molecules, but also constrain the origin of these mega-masers using the accurate locations of their emissions from ALMA for the first time.  With the kinematic and spatial constraints, we will also estimate the mass of the central supermassive black hole and study its feedback to the surrounding ISM.  These newly discovered mega-mesers potentially will open a new window for studying type II AGN in the coming years with fully operated ALMA.</prp:abstract>
